	Coldplay clearout    
	 London, Jan. 2 (PTI): British rock band Coldplay has raised $406,600 with an end-of-decade clearout sale.       
	The band put a load of old instruments, costumes and memorabilia up for sale on eBay over Christmas, raising close to half a million dollars, reports the Sun.      
	The Viva la Vida band raised the money for the charity Kids Company by selling off a series of items including the footwear they donned at the 2000 Glastonbury festival.       
	Six items each raised more than 10,000, with a guitar from the Viva La Vida tour selling for 15,000. Frontman Chris Martins first ever guitar and the four iconic jackets which the band made themselves and wore throughout their world tour were other items on sale.     
	Slim star    
	London (PTI): Popstar Christina Aguilera is the latest celebrity to have fallen for the size zero trend in Hollywood. The blonde bombshell once famed for her curvy figure looked emaciated during a recent public appearance. The 29-year-old singer cut a dramatically slim frame in Las Vegas.
                                                                                                                                                      
